https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;citusdata&#x2F;citus<p>I just realized this now, looks like Microsoft did it after they bought Citus? Good job!<p>Citus is a PostgreSQL extension that transforms Postgres into a distributed database.<p><pre><code>    -- before adding the first worker node, tell future worker nodes how to reach the coordinator
    SELECT citus_set_coordinator_host(&#x27;10.0.0.1&#x27;, 5432);

    -- add worker nodes
    SELECT citus_add_node(&#x27;10.0.0.2&#x27;, 5432);
    SELECT citus_add_node(&#x27;10.0.0.3&#x27;, 5432);

    -- rebalance the shards over the new worker nodes
    SELECT rebalance_table_shards();
</code></pre>
I am not affiliated with them, I just want to share this awesome OSS project.
